browser_type | "Description textarea" | text: "<description from external data>" | Textarea contains description | | 15 | browser_click | "Submit button" | — | Redirect to record-detail.html | | 16 | browser_wait_for | — | text: "✓" | Success toast appears | | 17 | browser_snapshot | — | — | Verify final state | | 18 | browser_click | "Submit for Review button" | — | Modal opens with confirmation dialog | | 19 | browser_type | "Workflow comment field" | text: "Automated submission — provisioning script" | Comment entered | | 20 | browser_click | "Confirm button" | — | Modal closes, status changes to Pending Review | | 21 | browser_wait_for | — | text: "Pending Review" | Status updated | | 22 | browser_click | "Approve button" | — | Approval modal opens | | 23 | browser_click | "Approve in modal" | — | Modal closes, status changes to Approved | | 24 | browser_wait_for | — | text: "✓" | Success toast appears | | 25 | browser_wait_for | — | text: "Approved" | Final status verified | ### How to Find Elements (Use browser_snapshot) These are HINTS from old scripts — the real UI may use different selectors or labels. After calling `browser_snapshot`, match elements using these clues (try in order): 1. **By data-testid** (most reliable if unchanged): - Username field → `data-testid="input-username"` - Password field → `data-testid="input-password"` - Sign In button → `data-testid="btn-login"` - Record Title field → `data-testid="input-record-title"` - Record Type dropdown → `data-testid="select-record-type"` - Assignee dropdown → `data-testid="select-record-assignee"` - Priority dropdown → `data-testid="select-record-priority"` - Due Date field → `data-testid="datepicker-record-due-date"` - Description textarea → `data-testid="textarea-record-description"` - Submit button → `data-testid="btn-submit-record"` - Submit for Review button → `data-testid="btn-submit-for-review"` - Approve button → `data-testid="btn-approve"` - Success toast → `data-testid="toast-success"` - Error toast → `data-testid="toast-error"` 2. **By visible label/text** (fallback if testids changed): - Look for input with label "Username" or "Email" - Look for input with label "Password" - Look for button with text "Sign In" or "Login" - Look for input with label "Title" or "Record Title" - Look for select with label "Type" or "Record Type" - Look for select with label "Assignee" - Look for select with label "Priority" - Look for input with label "Due Date" - Look for textarea with label "Description" - Look for button with text "Submit" or "Create Record" - Look for button with text "Submit for Review" - Look for button with text "Approve" - Look for toast notification with checkmark icon 3. **By role** (last resort): - Look for `role="textbox"` near label "Username" - Look for `role="textbox"` near label "Password" - Look for `role="button"` with name "Sign In" - Look for `role="combobox"` near label "Type" - Look for `role="combobox"` near label "Assignee" - Look for `role="combobox"` near label "Priority" - Look for `role="textbox"` near label "Due Date" - Look for `role="textbox"` near label "Description" - Look for `role="button"` with name "Submit" - Look for `role="button"` with name "Submit for Review" - Look for `role="button"` with name "Approve" - Look for `role="status"` with checkmark icon > ⚠️ If an element is NOT found in the snapshot, do NOT guess. Try `browser_take_screenshot` to visually inspect, or scroll with `browser_press_key` (PageDown) then `browser_snapshot` again. ### Fallback: browser_run_code If snapshot-based steps don't work, try this as a single `browser_run_code` call. NOTE: These selectors are estimated — they may need adjustment. ```js async (page) => { // Login await page.goto('http://localhost:8080/login.html'); await page.getByTestId('input-username').fill('admin'); await page.getByTestId('input-password').fill('admin123'); await page.getByTestId('btn-login').click(); await page.waitForURL(/dashboard/); // Fetch external data const response = await page.goto('http://localhost:8080/data.json'); const data = await response.json(); // Navigate to form await page.goto('http://localhost:8080/record-form.html'); // Fill form from API data await page.getByTestId('input-record-title').fill(data.title); await page.getByTestId('select-record-type').selectOption({ value: data.type }); await page.getByTestId('select-record-assignee').selectOption({ value: data.assignee }); await page.getByTestId('select-record-priority').selectOption({ value: data.priority }); await page.getByTestId('datepicker-record-due-date').fill(data.dueDate); await page.getByTestId('textarea-record-description').fill(data.description); // Submit form await page.getByTestId('btn-submit-record').click(); await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="toast-success"]'); // Submit for Review await page.getByTestId('btn-submit-for-review').click(); await page.getByTestId('btn-confirm-workflow').click(); await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="status-badge"]', { text: 'Pending Review' }); // Approve await page.getByTestId('btn-approve').click(); await page.getByTestId('btn-confirm-approval').click(); await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="status-badge"]', { text: 'Approved' }); await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="toast-success"]'); return { finalStatus: await page.textContent('[data-testid="status-badge"]'), successToast: await page.textContent('[data-testid="toast-success"]') }; } ``` ### Source (Old Selenium Scripts) - Primary: `scripts/test_automated_record_provisioning.py` (similarity: 0.417) — Full end-to-end workflow with external data integration, form submission, and approval process - Secondary: `scripts/test_approval_workflow.py` (similarity: 0.272) — Focused approval workflow with submit for review and approve steps ### Known Gaps — Things to Verify on Real Page - External data endpoint URL and response format may differ from `http://localhost:8080/data.json` - Form field names and data-testids may have changed since 